that are so well evidenced
that they're accepted across the board,

01:36:27.560 --> 01:36:30.564
even by skeptical
and non-Christian scholars.

01:36:30.720 --> 01:36:31.846
As a result, we...

01:36:31.960 --> 01:36:35.283
Now I understand what it is
you weren't allowed to talk about.

01:36:35.400 --> 01:36:38.882
I wish I still wasn't
allowed to talk about it.

01:36:39.000 --> 01:36:41.287
She needs me on that jury.

01:36:41.440 --> 01:36:42.885
Have faith, David.

01:36:43.000 --> 01:36:44.923
God's plan is at work.

01:36:45.040 --> 01:36:46.849
How'd you get here anyway?

01:36:46.960 --> 01:36:49.525
I borrowed your Prius.
It's very nice.

01:36:49.640 --> 01:36:52.728
Don't get too comfortable.
I'm planning a full recovery.

01:36:52.840 --> 01:36:55.566
So, Rice, do you believe that she
was proselytizing to her students?

01:36:55.680 --> 01:36:57.091
Governor, not at all.

01:36:57.200 --> 01:37:01.130
Jesus Christ was the most
influential person who ever lived.

01:37:01.240 --> 01:37:03.163
How could you ignore
that fact and teach history?

01:37:04.320 --> 01:37:05.651
I think the real problem is...

01:37:05.760 --> 01:37:07.410
Hey, Martin!

01:37:07.520 --> 01:37:08.885
More questions?

01:37:09.000 --> 01:37:10.496
I wanted to make sure that you were okay.

01:37:10.520 --> 01:37:12.124
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:37:12.240 --> 01:37:14.096
They're just holding me
over for a little observation.

01:37:14.120 --> 01:37:16.521
I'll be released soon.

01:37:16.680 --> 01:37:18.250
Something different about you.

01:37:18.360 --> 01:37:19.771
Are you okay?

01:37:19.880 --> 01:37:21.484
I should say so.

01:37:21.600 --> 01:37:23.602
Yes.

01:37:23.720 --> 01:37:25.484
I believe God wants me to be a minister,

01:37:25.600 --> 01:37:27.728
to return to my country
and become a pastor,

01:37:27.840 --> 01:37:29.080
just like you.

01:37:29.200 --> 01:37:30.690
That's great.

01:37:30.800 --> 01:37:32.928
There'll be challenges
in your country.

01:37:33.040 --> 01:37:35.520
Are you prepared for them?

01:37:37.000 --> 01:37:38.968
I am.

01:37:41.120 --> 01:37:42.531
I'm proud of you.

01:37:42.640 --> 01:37:44.051
Come here.

01:37:47.360 --> 01:37:48.725
That's awesome.

01:37:48.880 --> 01:37:51.566
It's a shocking reality
that Christians are soon gonna be forced

01:37:51.680 --> 01:37:55.927
to choose between obeying the law
of man or following the Word of God.

01:37:56.040 --> 01:37:57.485
I'm Mike Huckabee.

01:37:57.640 --> 01:37:59.369
We'll see you next time
on "Point of View."

01:38:27.880 --> 01:38:29.376
Hey, Brooke, why don't you
go be with Ms. Wesley.

01:38:29.400 --> 01:38:31.209
I think we can handle this.

01:38:31.320 --> 01:38:33.209
Yeah, seriously,
we've got backup coming.

01:38:33.320 --> 01:38:36.164
You're covered.

01:38:38.480 --> 01:38:40.084
Go get 'em.

01:38:44.800 --> 01:38:47.280
God's got this.

01:39:16.640 --> 01:39:18.927
Where's Tom?

01:39:23.880 --> 01:39:26.884
All rise.

01:39:33.720 --> 01:39:35.882
Be seated.

01:39:42.240 --> 01:39:43.651
Are we missing someone?

01:39:49.320 --> 01:39:50.970
Sorry, Your Honor.

01:39:51.080 --> 01:39:52.923
My apologies to the court.

01:39:57.320 --> 01:39:59.209
That's unexpected.

01:39:59.320 --> 01:40:01.482
He almost looks like a lawyer.

01:40:01.640 --> 01:40:06.123
Your Honor, I have
one final witness to call.

01:40:06.240 --> 01:40:09.369
Grace Wesley.

01:40:09.520 --> 01:40:13.481
Ms. Wesley,
please approach the witness stand.

01:40:13.600 --> 01:40:15.489
Do I have to?

01:40:15.600 --> 01:40:17.568
I'm afraid so.

01:40:22.200 --> 01:40:24.806
Your Honor, given the
witness's reluctance to testify,

01:40:24.920 --> 01:40:28.091
can I have the court's permission
to treat her as a hostile witness?

01:40:28.200 --> 01:40:32.524
You may. Proceed at your own peril.

01:40:35.640 --> 01:40:38.961
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth, and nothing but the truth?

01:40:39.080 --> 01:40:40.161
I do.

01:40:40.280 --> 01:40:41.691
Please be seated.

01:40:47.200 --> 01:40:49.487
Grace, I want you
to do something for me,

01:40:49.600 --> 01:40:52.285
something for everyone in this courtroom.

01:40:52.440 --> 01:40:54.522
I want you to apologize.

01:40:54.640 --> 01:40:57.405
I want you to say you're sorry
and that you made a mistake.

01:40:57.520 --> 01:40:58.816
Your Honor, what's going on here?

01:40:58.840 --> 01:41:01.241
Do it, Grace.

01:41:01.360 --> 01:41:02.850
I can't do that.

01:41:02.960 --> 01:41:04.883
Why? Why can't you do that, Grace?

01:41:05.000 --> 01:41:07.526
Because I don't believe
I did anything wrong.

01:41:07.640 --> 01:41:11.167
Well, as your attorney, I'm
advising you to do it anyway.

01:41:11.280 --> 01:41:15.407
To at least pretend that you're sorry and
throw yourself on the mercy of the court.

01:41:15.520 --> 01:41:16.567
What?

01:41:16.680 --> 01:41:18.091
That would be a lie.

01:41:18.200 --> 01:41:19.486
So what?

01:41:19.600 --> 01:41:20.965
Everyone lies.

01:41:21.080 --> 01:41:22.491
Not everyone.

01:41:22.600 --> 01:41:25.080
Are you looking to become a martyr?

01:41:25.200 --> 01:41:27.043
What in the world is he doing?

01:41:27.160 --> 01:41:28.730
I have no idea.

01:41:28.840 --> 01:41:29.727
No.

01:41:29.840 --> 01:41:31.205
Tommy...

01:41:31.320 --> 01:41:33.049
Then what is it that you want, Grace?

01:41:33.160 --> 01:41:36.369
Tell me. Tell us.

01:41:36.480 --> 01:41:37.845
I want...

01:41:39.920 --> 01:41:42.890
I want to be able to tell the truth.

01:41:43.000 --> 01:41:45.446
The truth?

01:41:45.560 --> 01:41:46.891
Whose truth?

01:41:47.000 --> 01:41:50.527
And what truth are you referring to?

01:41:50.640 --> 01:41:55.407
Grace, is there some truth that
you know that no one else knows?

01:41:57.520 --> 01:41:58.885
Oh, that's right.

01:41:59.000 --> 01:42:04.241
The other night, didn't you tell me
that Jesus spoke to you personally?

01:42:04.360 --> 01:42:05.850
Why are you doing this?

01:42:05.960 --> 01:42:07.576
I'm the one asking
the questions, Ms. Wesley.

01:42:07.600 --> 01:42:09.090
Did you or did you not tell me

01:42:09.200 --> 01:42:13.250
that Jesus spoke to you personally?

01:42:13.360 --> 01:42:15.806
Yes.

01:42:15.920 --> 01:42:18.207
And what did he say?

01:42:18.360 --> 01:42:20.089
I'll make it easier for you.

01:42:20.200 --> 01:42:22.806
Didn't you say that he
asked you a question?

01:42:22.920 --> 01:42:24.656
That was personal.
You weren't supposed to...

01:42:24.680 --> 01:42:26.330
I don't care.

01:42:26.440 --> 01:42:28.616
The other night, you told me
that Jesus asked you something.

01:42:28.640 --> 01:42:30.290
What did he ask you, Grace?

01:42:30.400 --> 01:42:31.811
Tell all of us.

01:42:31.920 --> 01:42:33.331
I think we deserve to know.

01:42:33.440 --> 01:42:35.044
Why are you doing this to me?

01:42:35.160 --> 01:42:36.525
Answer the question.

01:42:36.640 --> 01:42:38.210
They won't believe me.

01:42:38.320 --> 01:42:40.243
Doesn't matter.

01:42:40.360 --> 01:42:45.446
All that matters is that you believe it.

01:42:45.560 --> 01:42:48.723
Tell us, Grace, under penalty of perjury,

01:42:48.840 --> 01:42:51.764
what was the question that God
presented to you personally

01:42:51.880 --> 01:42:55.327
that night on campus?

01:42:55.480 --> 01:42:57.801
Answer the question.

01:42:59.920 --> 01:43:02.082
Answer the question!

01:43:08.600 --> 01:43:15.290
He asked, "Who do you say that I am?"

01:43:17.400 --> 01:43:21.962
And what did you answer?

01:43:22.080 --> 01:43:27.246
You are the Christ,
the Son of the living God.

01:43:31.200 --> 01:43:33.885
Well, there you have it.

01:43:34.000 --> 01:43:36.890
Your Honor, I think we've
all heard quite enough.

01:43:37.000 --> 01:43:40.881
Mr. Endler, are you
looking to change your client's plea?

01:43:41.000 --> 01:43:42.809
No, Your Honor.

01:43:42.920 --> 01:43:45.048
I say she's innocent of all wrongdoing.

01:43:45.160 --> 01:43:48.403
But I'm asking the jury
to find against her anyway.

01:43:48.520 --> 01:43:50.204
I mean, let's, let's face it.

01:43:50.320 --> 01:43:54.291
She has the audacity to believe
not only that there is a God,

01:43:54.400 --> 01:43:56.801
but that she has a personal
relationship with Him,

01:43:56.920 --> 01:44:00.367
which colors everything
that she says and does.

01:44:00.480 --> 01:44:04.168
I think it's time that we stop pretending
that we can trust a person like this

01:44:04.280 --> 01:44:06.328
to serve in a public capacity.

01:44:06.440 --> 01:44:09.922
In the name of tolerance
and diversity, I say we destroy her.

01:44:10.040 --> 01:44:11.326
That's enough, Mr. Endler.

01:44:11.440 --> 01:44:13.169
Then we can all go to our graves content,

01:44:13.280 --> 01:44:15.328
knowing that we stomped out
the last spark of faith

01:44:15.440 --> 01:44:17.200
that was ever exhibited
in the public square.

01:44:18.320 --> 01:44:19.606
That's enough, Mr. Endler.

01:44:19.720 --> 01:44:20.776
I say we make an example of her.

01:44:20.800 --> 01:44:22.609
Mr. Endler, that's enough.

01:44:22.720 --> 01:44:26.966
Let's set a new precedent, that employment
by our federal government mandates

01:44:27.080 --> 01:44:29.731
that you must first denounce
any belief system you have.

01:44:29.840 --> 01:44:31.616
Mr. Endler that is enough!
You are out of order.

01:44:31.640 --> 01:44:33.369
And if someone slips through the cracks

01:44:33.480 --> 01:44:37.769
and hides their beliefs,
then we arrest them and fine them.

01:44:37.880 --> 01:44:39.856
And if they don't pay,
then we seize their property.

01:44:39.880 --> 01:44:41.211
And if they resist...

01:44:42.680 --> 01:44:44.045
Well, let's not kid ourselves.

01:44:44.160 --> 01:44:46.003
Enforcement is always at the end of a gun.

01:44:46.120 --> 01:44:47.884
Mr. Endler, you are out of order.

01:44:48.000 --> 01:44:49.331
I charge you with contempt!

01:44:49.440 --> 01:44:53.771
I accept the charge, because I have
nothing but contempt for these proceedings.

01:44:53.880 --> 01:44:56.770
If we're going to insist that
a Christian's right to believe

01:44:56.880 --> 01:45:00.962
is subordinate to all other rights,
then it's not a right.

01:45:01.080 --> 01:45:03.686
Somebody is always going to be offended.

01:45:03.800 --> 01:45:06.690
Two thousand years of
human history proves that.

01:45:06.800 --> 01:45:08.484
So, I say we get on with it.

01:45:08.600 --> 01:45:11.922
Cite the law, charge the jury,
and send them off to deliberate.

01:45:12.040 --> 01:45:14.008
So be it!

01:45:17.880 --> 01:45:21.441
Now, we are gonna bypass
the usual closing arguments,

01:45:21.560 --> 01:45:24.962
unless Mr. Kane finds the need
to further address the jury.

01:45:25.080 --> 01:45:26.969
No, Your Honor.

01:45:27.080 --> 01:45:29.367
We can ask nothing more.

01:45:29.480 --> 01:45:33.371
My instructions to you are simple.

01:45:33.480 --> 01:45:37.804
Uphold the law without unfairly
prejudicing your decision

01:45:37.920 --> 01:45:42.528
or risking a mistrial on appeal.

01:45:42.640 --> 01:45:48.522
Now, I believe I can safely say
that the respondent's counsel

01:45:48.640 --> 01:45:53.726
has dared you to convict his own client.

01:45:57.680 --> 01:46:01.480
The jury will now be
dismissed for deliberation.

01:46:01.600 --> 01:46:04.729
We are adjourned.

01:46:11.080 --> 01:46:13.401
She hasn't got a prayer.

01:46:13.520 --> 01:46:14.851
Let's go.

01:46:18.200 --> 01:46:20.931
Remind me to send him a thank-you note.

01:47:26.480 --> 01:47:28.289
Thank you so much.
Thank you, guys.

01:47:28.400 --> 01:47:29.731
Thanks for coming out.

01:47:29.880 --> 01:47:33.922
